Biography:

California native Presley Hart made her first movies in 2011 and quickly got the attention of fans with her all-natural body and good looks that might remind you of a sorority girl. OMG I Fucked My Daughter's BFF 2 from Devil's Film was one of Presley's first movies. She landed the cover photo thanks to her looks, but the charm and "innocent" sensuality she displays in the scene proves that even in those early days this girl was one to watch. In summer 2012 Presley starred in the romantic feature Diary of Love from Smash Pictures, based on the hugely popular The Notebook. As Ally, who rekindles the old flame with her high school love Noah (Richie Calhoun), Presley owned the movie and was stunning to watch. She was beautiful, hot, and she could even act â€” a triple threat in the adult film world. Presley was one of the reasons Diary of Love proved to be a hit, but being in an erotic adaptation of one of the most popular "chick flicks" of the last decade did a lot for Presley's popularity, too. Women who watch porn with their partners or on their own could appreciate a girl like Presley, who could bring a romantic character like Ally to life. When Girl Candy Films released the taboo-shattering Mother Superior three months later, Presley was once again on a lot of adult film viewers' minds. As a young nun who prays with fellow Sister Ariella Ferrara that they might overcome their sinful lust for one another, Presley plays a big part of in one of 2012's most talked-about lesbian movies. Presley was named Unsung Female Performer of the Year at the 2014 AVN Awards.
